      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/224/1",
      "text": [
        ": مَنْ قَرَأَ سُورَهَ التَّغَابُنِ فِی فَرِیضَهٍ کَانَتْ شَفِیعَهً لَهُ یَوْمَ الْقِیَامَهِ وَ شَاهِدَ عَدْلٍ عِنْدَ مَنْ یُجِیزُ شَهَادَتَهَا ثُمَّ لَا یُفَارِقُهَا حَتَّی یَدْخُلَ الْجَنَّهَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "1. From the previous chain from al-Hassan from al-Hussain b. Abi al-’Ala from Abi Basir from Abi Abdillah (a.s.) who said: One who recites Surah Taghabun in his obligatory prayers it will intercede for him on the Day of Judgment, offer evidence for him in justice, near one who considers its testimony justified for himself, it would not separate from him till it has him admitted in Paradise."
        ]
      }
    },
